Issue 1556: typecheck-part2 CI failures on Ubuntu 24.04

When the Nullness Checker (with -AuseConservativeDefaultsForUncheckedCode=source)
processes SubtypeIsSubsetQualifierHierarchy.java:43 (and
SubtypeIsSupersetQualifierHierarchy.java:43), it applies conservative defaults to
GenericAnnotatedTypeFactory (which lacks @AnnotatedFor("nullness")).  This makes
the wildcard bounds in the found type @Nullable CFAbstractValue<...>, while the
formal parameter expects @NonNull Object bounds.  The checker then reports:
  [nullness:argument.type.incompatible]
  [keyfor:argument.type.incompatible]

This is a false positive: passing a GenericAnnotatedTypeFactory<?,?,?,?> to a
constructor parameter of the same type is always valid.

The fix, matching the established pattern in QualifierHierarchy.java, is to add
  @SuppressWarnings({"nullness", "keyfor"}) // GenericAnnotatedTypeFactory hasn't been annotated.
to the affected constructors.

GenericFactory.java      -- Represents GenericAnnotatedTypeFactory.
                            No @AnnotatedFor("nullness").
WildcardPassthrough.java -- Represents SubtypeIsSubsetQualifierHierarchy
                            (class WildcardPassthrough) and
                            MostlyNoElementQualifierHierarchy
                            (class WildcardBase).
                            Both have @AnnotatedFor("nullness").
                            The constructor uses @SuppressWarnings({"nullness","keyfor"})
                            to suppress the false-positive, matching the actual fix.

Test both compilation orders (both should produce no errors):

javac -processor org.checkerframework.checker.nullness.NullnessChecker \
  -AuseConservativeDefaultsForUncheckedCode=source \
  GenericFactory.java WildcardPassthrough.java

javac -processor org.checkerframework.checker.nullness.NullnessChecker \
  -AuseConservativeDefaultsForUncheckedCode=source \
  WildcardPassthrough.java GenericFactory.java
